    @schema.validate(output_schema={
        "type": "object",
    })
    def get(self, id):
        object = some_find_object(id)

        if object is None:
            self.error("Object not found")
        else:
            return object
```

I want to return `object` type if object is found and output error Jsend status if it's not.
According to [validate()](https://github.com/hfaran/Tornado-JSON/blob/master/tornado_json/schema.py#L16) implementation it's currently impossible.

