To deal with various datetime formats, I would define the following functions:

```python
def parseRFC1123(RFC1123_datetime_string):
  return native_datetime_object

def parse14Digit(14Digit_datetime_string):
  return native_datetime_object

def to14Digit(native_datetime_object):
  return "14Digit_datetime_string"

def toRFC1123(native_datetime_object):
  return "RFC1123_datetime_string"
```

These can be reused in many ways as individual helper functions and also as composite functions for example to convert HTTP DateTime to 14-digit format, either two functions can be called inline in sequence or wrapped in another function as following:

```python
def RFC1123To14Digit(RFC1123_datetime_string):
  return to14Digit(parseRFC1123(RFC1123_datetime_string))
```

